    loop invariant i2;
    loop variant v1;
*/
```

Use the ACSL syntax to provide the variant and invariants: the loop invariants must be preceeded by the "//@ loop invariant" annotations and the loop variant must be preceeded by the "//@ loop variant" annotation.

